### StudyOS API Test Suite
### VS Code REST Client Extension
### Run each request individually with "Send Request"
### Install: ritwickdey.rest-client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@contentType = application/json

@docId = PASTE_DOCUMENT_ID_HERE
@quizId = PASTE_QUIZ_ID_HERE
@questionId = PASTE_QUESTION_ID_HERE
@flashcardId = PASTE_FLASHCARD_ID_HERE
@gameId = PASTE_GAME_ID_HERE
@subject = General
@sessionId = test-session-1


# 0. HEALTH CHECK

### 0.1 — Server health + service status
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

# 1. DOCUMENTS

### 1.1 — List all documents
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents

### 1.2 — Upload a plain text document (no binary file needed)
# To test PDF/DOCX upload, use the file variable below
# Change the file path to a real file on your machine
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="subject"

{{subject}}
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test-note.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Photosynthesis is the process by which green plants and some other organisms use sunlight to synthesise foods from carbon dioxide and water. Photosynthesis in plants generally involves the green pigment chlorophyll and generates oxygen as a byproduct.

The light-dependent reactions occur in the thylakoid membranes. They use light energy to produce ATP and NADPH.

The light-independent reactions, also called the Calvin cycle, occur in the stroma. They use the ATP and NADPH from the light-dependent reactions to fix carbon dioxide into glucose.

Cellular respiration is the reverse of photosynthesis. Glucose and oxygen are converted to carbon dioxide, water, and ATP energy.

Mitosis is the process of cell division in which one cell divides to produce two genetically identical daughter cells. It occurs in somatic cells.

Meiosis is the process of cell division that produces gametes. It reduces the chromosome number by half and introduces genetic variation.
------Boundary--

### 1.3 — Get a specific document by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/{{docId}}

### 1.4 — Delete a document
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/documents/{{docId}}


###############################################
# 2. CHAT
###############################################

### 2.1 — Basic chat message (default mode)
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What is photosynthesis?",
  "subject": "{{subject}}",
  "session_id": "{{sessionId}}"
}

### 2.2 — Chat in "explain simply" mode
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Explain the difference between mitosis and meiosis",
  "subject": "{{subject}}",
  "mode": "explain",
  "session_id": "{{sessionId}}"
}

### 2.3 — Chat in "step by step" mode
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Walk me through how the Calvin cycle works",
  "subject": "{{subject}}",
  "mode": "step_by_step",
  "session_id": "{{sessionId}}"
}

### 2.4 — Chat in "lecturer" mode
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Give me an academic overview of cellular respiration",
  "subject": "{{subject}}",
  "mode": "lecturer",
  "session_id": "{{sessionId}}"
}

### 2.5 — Chat in "exam revision" mode
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What are the key facts I need to know about photosynthesis for an exam?",
  "subject": "{{subject}}",
  "mode": "exam_revision",
  "session_id": "{{sessionId}}"
}

### 2.6 — Get chat history for a session
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/history?session_id={{sessionId}}&limit=20

### 2.7 — Get chat history with custom limit
GET {{baseUrl}}/chat/history?session_id={{sessionId}}&limit=5

### 2.8 — Clear chat history for a session
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/chat/history?session_id={{sessionId}}


